Statements: the acquisition of tert promoter mutation in braf or nras mutated melanoma probably allows the re-expression of tert leading to the immortalization process on path to melanoma development, together with other alterations such as inactivation of cyclin dependent kinase inhibitor 2a (cdkn2a).

xref_bibr, xref_bibr another preclinical study demonstrated that the combination of selumetinib and a mammalian target of rapamycin (mtor) inhibitor (azd8055) which is downstream of pi3k and akt pathway, induces tumor regression in braf mutant uveal melanoma cell lines but not gnaq mutant cell lines.
